Key Match Events: Anthony Edwards struggled offensively, shooting 6-for-23 from the field and finishing with 16 points
Pre-Game Insights: The Timberwolves traded Karl-Anthony Towns to the New York Knicks in exchange for Julius Randle and Donte DiVincenzo
Post-Match Reflections: Anthony Edwards praised DiVincenzo, saying Knicks fans would miss him
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rudy Gobert was dominant inside, posting 13 points and 17 rebounds
Lonzo Ball, making his return after two years, impressed with 10 points in 15 minutes, shooting 4-for-6 from the field, including two 3-pointers
